&lt;h2&gt;Company Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Eon is revolutionizing the enormous and rapidly growing cloud infrastructure resiliency industry for enterprise customers. It is led by the team that founded CloudEndure (Cloud Disaster Recovery and Migration startup, acquired by AWS), and subsequently built two native AWS services, AWS Elastic Disaster Recovery, and AWS Application Migration Service, supporting the world&#39;s largest enterprises. Eon is backed by Sequoia, Lightspeed, among other prominent investors. We are currently seeking an exceptional Senior Sales Engineer to join our fast growing team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Position Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Eon is seeking a highly technical and customer-facing Senior Sales Engineer with expertise in cloud infrastructure solutions to join our team. In this role, you will operate as the real-time technical partner to Account Executives across a territory, leading discovery and qualification, tailoring demos, sizing opportunities with clear ROI, and guiding prospects through evaluations and pilots. You dive deeply into technical details with customer teams, map solutions to business outcomes, and build strong, trusted relationships. Collaborating closely with AEs, Solution Architects, product, and engineering, you proactively identify gaps, capture structured feedback, and translate it into crisp business and technical requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary technical partner to Account Executives for prospective customers evaluating Eon. Lead technical discovery and qualification, disqualifying when there is no technical fit.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate how Eon addresses customer use cases with tailored demos; build compelling business cases and ROI analyses that align value to the customer’s context.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Address day-to-day technical questions, security basics, and common objections.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Account Executives to understand requirements; configure Eon capabilities to showcase fit and define measurable success criteria.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educate and share best practices with customers by leading and owning the development, delivery, review, and maintenance of technical content (e.g., demo assets, sample configs, presentations, white papers, public sessions).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel occasionally to customer sites for demos, workshops, evaluation support, and relationship building.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify product feedback from customers, spotting trends and surfacing insights to help shape the roadmap and influence how our tech evolves.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Qualifications&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Significant experience in a pre-sales role (Sales Engineer/Field Engineer) working with enterprise customers on cloud infrastructure, storage, data protection, or adjacent platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with one or more public cloud provider (AWS/Azure/GCP) technologies from a dev/ops perspective (e.g., networking, security, compute, IAM).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced technical skills, including the ability to troubleshoot complex issues and to design and present practical solution architectures; proven ability to run/manage standard POCs and pilots.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and storytelling skills, including tailoring demos and articulating ROI/business cases to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent team working skills, with the ability to collaborate effectively with Account Executives, Solution Architects, product, and engineering in a fast-paced, dynamic environment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Readiness to work in a highly intense startup environment requiring extreme focus, a strong sense of ownership, and persistence to breakthrough.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Availability to travel in US - 30%&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;

&lt;h2&gt;Company Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Eon is revolutionizing the enormous and rapidly growing cloud infrastructure resiliency industry for enterprise customers. It is led by the team that founded CloudEndure (Cloud Disaster Recovery and Migration startup, acquired by AWS), and subsequently built two native AWS services, AWS Elastic Disaster Recovery, and AWS Application Migration Service, supporting the world&#39;s largest enterprises. Eon is backed by Sequoia, Lightspeed, among other prominent investors. We are currently seeking an exceptional Senior Sales Engineer to join our fast growing team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Position Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Eon is seeking a highly technical and customer-facing Senior Sales Engineer with expertise in cloud infrastructure solutions to join our team. In this role, you will operate as the real-time technical partner to Account Executives across a territory, leading discovery and qualification, tailoring demos, sizing opportunities with clear ROI, and guiding prospects through evaluations and pilots. You dive deeply into technical details with customer teams, map solutions to business outcomes, and build strong, trusted relationships. Collaborating closely with AEs, Solution Architects, product, and engineering, you proactively identify gaps, capture structured feedback, and translate it into crisp business and technical requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary technical partner to Account Executives for prospective customers evaluating Eon. Lead technical discovery and qualification, disqualifying when there is no technical fit.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate how Eon addresses customer use cases with tailored demos; build compelling business cases and ROI analyses that align value to the customer’s context.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Address day-to-day technical questions, security basics, and common objections.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Account Executives to understand requirements; configure Eon capabilities to showcase fit and define measurable success criteria.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educate and share best practices with customers by leading and owning the development, delivery, review, and maintenance of technical content (e.g., demo assets, sample configs, presentations, white papers, public sessions).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel occasionally to customer sites for demos, workshops, evaluation support, and relationship building.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify product feedback from customers, spotting trends and surfacing insights to help shape the roadmap and influence how our tech evolves.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Qualifications&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Significant experience in a pre-sales role (Sales Engineer/Field Engineer) working with enterprise customers on cloud infrastructure, storage, data protection, or adjacent platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with one or more public cloud provider (AWS/Azure/GCP) technologies from a dev/ops perspective (e.g., networking, security, compute, IAM).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced technical skills, including the ability to troubleshoot complex issues and to design and present practical solution architectures; proven ability to run/manage standard POCs and pilots.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and storytelling skills, including tailoring demos and articulating ROI/business cases to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent team working skills, with the ability to collaborate effectively with Account Executives, Solution Architects, product, and engineering in a fast-paced, dynamic environment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Readiness to work in a highly intense startup environment requiring extreme focus, a strong sense of ownership, and persistence to breakthrough.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Availability to travel in US - 30%&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;

&lt;p&gt;Hi. I’m Ron, Eon’s co-founder and CTO.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I’ll be direct: Eon is at the most crucial moment in its journey, and we are looking for highly skilled engineers to help bring this company to the next stage. We’ve done what no one else has managed to do - make backups actually useful, building a cloud-native backup and recovery platform for enterprises running across multi-cloud environments. Eon turns backup data into a strategic asset, with visibility, control, and usability across the board. We’re trusted by global enterprises, and we’re building a once-in-a-generation company. &lt;br&gt;In other words: NOW&amp;nbsp; is the time to join us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a Senior Backend Developer who is ready to build at the highest level. You&#39;ll design and scale backend systems that power the core of our platform. You&#39;ll work directly with me to deliver features that enterprises can&#39;t live without. You&#39;ll work with top talent like yourself - with opportunities for peer learning and the chance to mentor others. We&#39;re looking for people who approach challenges as opportunities to develop solutions. Here, you&#39;ll have the opportunity to drive innovation from within and shape the way in which we develop.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not a role where you&#39;re buried in bureaucracy. You&#39;ll see your work ship quickly, shape the company itself, and directly impact how Fortune 500 companies handle their most critical cloud infrastructure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build backend services that can scale across multi-cloud environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work directly with other engineers and product leads to deliver end-to-end solutions that matter.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Push performance to the limit - speed, reliability, and security at enterprise scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write code you’re proud of: clean, testable, maintainable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make key architecture and design decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring your perspective straight to me and - I want your voice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate with autonomy and own your own work. (I mean it.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Must-Haves&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are the best in your team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You want to work with the very best.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You thrive when you’re trusted with real ownership and responsibility.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You move quickly, collaborate well, and know how to make an impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re hyper-motivated to build something epic.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice-to-Haves&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with AWS, Azure, GCP, or all of the above.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort working in high-scale, data-heavy environments where performance matters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Join Us?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Eon is the fastest growing startup in cloud infrastructure and cyber security. We are extremely well-funded, trusted by the biggest players in the industry. But we’re also lean, agile, and flat. You’ll work directly with me and be part of the founding team, shape product direction, and see your work change the trajectory of enterprises around the world. We demand a lot because what we’re building is big.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We take care of our people, and we make sure your journey here will be enjoyable and worth the ride.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re ready to be part of an incredible team and do the best work of your career, now’s&amp;nbsp; the time to apply&lt;strong&gt;, even if your experience doesn’t tick every box. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Eon, we’re transforming cloud backups into useful assets for the first time ever. Backed by prominent investors and industry leaders, our groundbreaking Cloud Backup Posture Management (CBPM) platform offers instant visibility and access across all cloud environments, turning every backup into a searchable, accessible tool. We’re an ambitious, collaborative team driven to redefine what’s possible in cloud technology. Join us, and see how your contributions can directly shape the future of backup.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a skilled and client-oriented Solutions Architect with expertise in cloud infrastructure to join our team. In this role, you’ll design and implement Eon’s cloud backup solution to meet the business goals of the companies we work with, while building strong, trusted relationships with them. You&#39;ll be responsible for driving technical discussions, working closely with both clients and development teams, identifying key gaps in our products and services, and translating feedback into clear business and technical requirements for our product and engineering teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary technical advisor for enterprises evaluating Eon. Demonstrate how Eon can address their use cases through proofs of concept, providing technical guidance on integration, deployment, and best practices for adoption.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with account executives to understand client requirements and configure Eon’s capabilities to showcase how it meets their needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead new client onboarding, mapping their business needs, and designing Eon’s solution to solve their problems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise on the best tracking implementation strategies and guide clients through the process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and share best practices with clients by developing technical content such as sample code, blog posts, presentations, white papers, and workshops.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel occasionally for workshops, implementation support, and relationship building with clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gather client feedback, identify trends, and share insights to influence product roadmaps and drive tech evolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;You have significant experience working with enterprises on cloud infrastructure products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’ve worked with at least one public cloud provider (AWS, Azure, GCP) from a dev/ops perspective.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have advanced technical skills and can troubleshoot complex problems while designing and implementing custom solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re an excellent communicator, able to explain technical concepts clearly to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You thrive in a fast-paced, dynamic startup environment and work well with cross-functional teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re willing to travel up to 30% within the US.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Join Us?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Be part of a passionate and innovative team driving change in the cloud backup space.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity for professional growth in a fast-paced startup environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive salary and benefits package.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 data-start=&quot;155&quot; data-end=&quot;170&quot;&gt;About Eon&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;171&quot; data-end=&quot;473&quot;&gt;Eon is building a modern, cloud-native data protection platform designed for today’s infrastructure. We help companies protect and recover their data at scale—without legacy complexity. Our customers are technology-forward teams dealing with real production challenges across cloud, data, and security.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;475&quot; data-end=&quot;599&quot;&gt;We’re a hands-on company that values ownership, technical depth, and people who want to build and improve things end to end.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr data-start=&quot;601&quot; data-end=&quot;604&quot;&gt;
&lt;h3 data-start=&quot;606&quot; data-end=&quot;626&quot;&gt;About the Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;627&quot; data-end=&quot;836&quot;&gt;We’re looking for a Technical Customer Success Manager with strong cloud and infrastructure experience and a commercial mindset. This is a deeply technical, hands-on role—not a project management CSM position.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;838&quot; data-end=&quot;1142&quot;&gt;You’ll own the full customer lifecycle, from technical onboarding through adoption, expansion, and renewal. You’ll work directly in customer cloud environments, build lightweight technical solutions, and help customers get value from EON quickly, while identifying opportunities to grow the relationship.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1144&quot; data-end=&quot;1256&quot;&gt;The role reports to the Head of CS &amp;amp; Support and works closely with Sales Engineering, Product, and Engineering.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr data-start=&quot;1258&quot; data-end=&quot;1261&quot;&gt;
&lt;h3 data-start=&quot;1263&quot; data-end=&quot;1283&quot;&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul data-start=&quot;1284&quot; data-end=&quot;2154&quot;&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1284&quot; data-end=&quot;1393&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1286&quot; data-end=&quot;1393&quot;&gt;Own technical onboarding for new customers, including cloud environment setup, demos, and implementations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1394&quot; data-end=&quot;1486&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1396&quot; data-end=&quot;1486&quot;&gt;Build scripts, configurations, and small technical solutions to accelerate time-to-value&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1487&quot; data-end=&quot;1569&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1489&quot; data-end=&quot;1569&quot;&gt;Serve as the primary technical contact for a portfolio of enterprise customers&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1570&quot; data-end=&quot;1661&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1572&quot; data-end=&quot;1661&quot;&gt;Run ongoing check-ins, QBRs, and executive reviews to drive adoption and identify risks&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1662&quot; data-end=&quot;1734&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1664&quot; data-end=&quot;1734&quot;&gt;Troubleshoot and resolve complex issues with Support and Engineering&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1735&quot; data-end=&quot;1801&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1737&quot; data-end=&quot;1801&quot;&gt;Own renewals and renewal forecasting for your book of business&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1802&quot; data-end=&quot;1886&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1804&quot; data-end=&quot;1886&quot;&gt;Identify and qualify expansion opportunities (upsell, cross-sell, new use cases)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1887&quot; data-end=&quot;1953&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1889&quot; data-end=&quot;1953&quot;&gt;Partner with Account Executives on account planning and growth&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1954&quot; data-end=&quot;2021&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1956&quot; data-end=&quot;2021&quot;&gt;Work with Sales Engineers during pre-sales and expansion cycles&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;2022&quot; data-en
